# Cybersecurity Day 8 – Malware & Cyberwarfare

## External Threats
External threats are attackers outside an organization.
They may be amateurs or skilled attackers who exploit
vulnerabilities in networks and systems.

---

## Cyberwarfare
Cyberwarfare is the use of technology by one nation to
penetrate and attack another nation’s computer systems
and networks.

Its goal may include:
- Causing damage
- Disrupting services
- Shutting down critical infrastructure such as power grids

---

## Attacks: Concepts and Techniques
Understanding how attacks are planned and executed helps
security professionals analyze and defend against them.

---

## Malware
Malware is any malicious software or code designed to:
- Steal data
- Bypass access controls
- Damage or compromise systems

Attackers often use different types of malware to carry out attacks.

---

## Spyware
Spyware is malware that:
- Tracks and monitors online activities
- Records user behavior
- May log keystrokes (keylogging)
- Steals sensitive personal data

---

## Adware
Adware is software designed to automatically display or
deliver advertisements to users, most often through web browsers.
